cuems-utils (0.1.0rc10) unstable; urgency=medium

  * deps: bump lxml 5.3.0 -> 6.1.0 to clear CVE-2026-41066 (high) -- XXE via
    iterparse()/ETCompatXMLParser() with resolve_entities=True default (fixed:
    default is now 'internal'). cuems-utils only uses lxml.etree.Element +
    register_namespace (never the parser entry points), so it was never
    actually reachable, but bumped to clear the advisory and future-proof.
    Full test suite verified green before (5.3.0) and after (6.1.0): 312
    passed, XML round-trips included. Ships the same source as main/rc_1 @
    0.1.0rc10 (media-duration + node-identity + gradient_osc_port).

 -- Ion Reguera <ion@stagelab.coop>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 20:20:09 +0200

cuems-utils (0.1.0rc9) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Media duration correctness (paired with the cuems-editor + cuems-frontend
    fixes for the ffprobe duration-extraction bug):
    - cues/MediaCue: Media.duration is validated and canonicalised on write
      (accepts str/CTimecode/None, rejects malformed); the getter contract
      stays str so engine consumers (CTimecode(cue.media.duration)) are
      unchanged.
    - xml/schemas/script.xsd: escape the literal dot in TimecodeType and
      constrain MediaType/duration from unbounded xs:string to the
      pattern-validated cms:TimecodeType (plain text, no structural change;
      existing/repaired XMLs still validate, malformed values now rejected).
    - tests: add tests/unit/test_media_duration.py (8 tests).

 -- Ion Reguera <ion@stagelab.coop>  Mon, 06 Jul 2026 20:34:53 +0200

cuems-utils (0.1.0rc8) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Package pre_release_1 code (merged into debian/bookworm). Notable
    changes since 0.1.0rc5:
    - xml/schemas/network_map.xsd: optional node-identity fields
      (role_id, alias, hostname) for the nodeconf identity model.
    - settings.{xml,xsd}: add gradient_osc_port (needed by cuems-engine
      pre_release_1); add output_latency_ms tri-state to player types;
      per-node settings.xml template.
    - CTimecode: >24h MTC correctness fixes (skip_rollover __str__,
      None-safe comparators + __hash__ dedupe, dict-compatible items()),
      and .milliseconds -> _rounded/_exact split migrated across
      AudioCue/VideoCue/DmxCue.
    - cues/VideoCue: remove deprecated video_media_loop.
    - pyproject: pin lxml (CVE-2026-41066 context documented).

 -- Ion Reguera <ion@stagelab.coop>  Mon, 06 Jul 2026 17:31:30 +0200

